reviews.review: Although visually it was an amazing movie with outstanding scenery, it was the final nail in the coffin when it comes to a true Star Wars film. As someone who loves Star Wars it was all just messed up.

Does everything it can to right the ship after the debacle of The Last Jedi. Unfortunately the damage had already been done and the final chapter of the Skywalker saga feels rushed and disjointed while it attempts to rebuild an interesting story.

Too many holes.  Dumb that she just changed her name at the end.  Meaningless.  Seems like they were more interested in big special effects than a good story line.  The other supreme leader in 2 already said he was the one connecting the two of them, and then suddenly they're a duality in the force?  Dumb.  Watch your own movies.
It was very well done and wound up the story in a respectful way.
Good closure to an epic series.  Only a couple of things  I disliked but it is just personal preference and not wanting to give any spoilers.  Very good movie
Movie was great!  Great action and story and complex characters - well done JJ!
it was fun, but dont scrutinize too much. dont expect classic star wars and you will have a good time.

Long have I waited....to review Rise of Skywalker.  Ha!  See what I did there?
What a great Star Wars movie, in the top 3 for sure, right after Return of the Jedi as number one, of course, then Revenge of the Sith a close second and now Rise of Skywalker coming in at 3.
All of the answers you wanted are in this movie, a great conclusion to our 42 year journey!
It will take a few viewings to catch all of the action and all of the plot details in this one, I am still thinking about it all and can't wait to see it again!
An awesome movie that does a great job of ending the trilogy.  Great graphics and just the right amount of cuteness without any stupid jarjar binks stupidity.
I just can't say that it's a great movie. It wasn't necessarily horrible either. The story moves too quick and is a complete mess. A lot of cool eye candy though. I liked it...
